Done! The ODE solver is implemented at `/app/ode_solve.py`. 

**Key features:**
- Uses RK4 (4th-order Runge-Kutta) for integration
- Step size: h_max/2 = (t1-t0)/400 to satisfy the multi-stage safe bound
- Lands exactly at each eval_t with final substep clamped
- Evaluates `rhs` at each landing time (no interpolation)
- Outputs `/app/output/solution.csv` with `t,y` format
- Pure NumPy implementation (no black-box ODE libraries)

The solver will be tested against the harness-provided `ode_problem.py` which defines `t0`, `t1`, `y0`, `eval_ts`, and `rhs(t,y)`.
